        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 5:08PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Fine, or 20 miles north of Old Forge, moving northeast
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Nehasane, Robinwood, Lyon Lake, Lake Lila, Sabattis, and Partlow.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
